parties.raw_snippet: This SPONSORSHIP AND SERVICES AGREEMENT (the “Agreement”) is made and entered into as of the 19th day of December, 2018, by and among HOF Village, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“HOFV”), National Football Museum, Inc., d/b/a Pro Football Hall of Fame, an Ohio corporation (“PFHOF” and, together with HOFV, the “HOF Entities”) and Constellation NewEnergy, Inc., a Delaware corporation, on behalf of itself and its retail affiliates and subsidiaries (collectively, “Constellation”). HOFV and/or PFHOF, on the one hand, and Constellation, on the other hand, are referred to herein as a “Party” and, collectively, as the “Parties”.
parties.reasoning: The quoted paragraph in the preamble explicitly names the contracting entities and their corporate forms and trade names; it identifies the three main parties to the Agreement.
normalized_value: National Football Museum, Inc. d/b/a Pro Football Hall of Fame

contract_type.raw_snippet:
SPONSORSHIP AND SERVICES AGREEMENT

WHEREAS, Constellation desires to become a sponsor of the Village and to obtain the rights set forth herein in connection with such sponsorship.
contract_type.reasoning: The document title describes the agreement as a 'Sponsorship and Services' agreement and the WHEREAS clause expressly states Constellation's desire to become a sponsor and obtain sponsorship rights. Substantively the contract grants sponsorship/branding rights to Constellation in exchange for sponsorship fees and also sets out Constellation's obligation to provide products and services (energy-related supply and services). The primary commercial exchange centers on sponsorship/branding rights plus related service/supply obligations, so 'Sponsorship Agreement' best captures the primary purpose.

notice_period.reasoning: The contract does not contain any clause stating that the agreement will automatically renew unless notice is given, nor does it specify an advance notice period to prevent renewal. The Term is a fixed calendar end date (December 31, 2028) with no automatic renewal language.

expiration_date.raw_snippet: The term of this Agreement (the “Term”), unless mutually extended by written agreement of the Parties or unless sooner terminated as provided herein, shall commence effective as of the date hereof and shall expire on December 31, 2028.
expiration_date.reasoning: Section 4.1 explicitly states the agreement's expiration as a calendar date: 'shall expire on December 31, 2028.' This is an explicit calendar date so it can be normalized to ISO format.

renewal_term.reasoning: There is no language in the Agreement providing for automatic renewal or specifying renewal terms (only that the Term may be 'mutually extended by written agreement of the Parties'). Therefore no renewal term is specified.
